comment_data.body:
Should I implement pymutex.can_check_locked() capability check:

```c
static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_Locks_PyMutex_SupportsLocked(void) {
    // Python < 3.13: PyMutex doesn't exist
    #if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030d0000
        return 0;
    
    #else
        // Limited API mode that doesn't have locked()
        #ifdef Py_LIMITED_API
            return 0;
        #else
            return 1;
        #endif
    #endif
}


```

Of course in 3.15 and later we should revisit depending on changes.

